Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with the @dried oregano{1%sachet}.
Drizzle with @olive oil, season with @salt and @black pepper, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in the #sieve{} and pop half of them into
another #bowl{}. Crush the black beans in the bowl using a #potato masher{}.
Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot,
add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and @sweetcorn{160%grams} and cook until the
corn is charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice
during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Once the corn is charred, add the black beans (whole and mashed),
@Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} and @garlic clove{1} to the pan.
Season with @salt and @pepper, stir well and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water for the beans{75%milliliter} and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}.
Stir together, bring to a simmer and cook until the liquid has evaporated,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove the pan from the heat, then stir through the cheese. Taste and season
with @salt and @pepper if needed.

Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} onto a baking tray and spoon
the filling onto one half of each one. Fold the other side over to make a
semi-circle. Press down to keep together. Drizzle a little @olive oil over the top,
then bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-12%minutes}.

== Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%milliliter} with the
@sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt and
@pepper and mix to combine.

== To Serve ==

When the quesadillas are ready, add the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} to the dressing.
Toss to combine.

> TIP: Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

Divide your quesadillas between #plates{}.

Serve with the herby chips and salad. Add the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} alongside to
finish.

Enjoy!